Welcome to my twisted mind..
I’m Jessica and thanks for reading my blog! I’m an almost 25 year old
Chinese American living in Seattle but originally from Virginia.
Currently, I’m a 4th year PhD student at the University of Washington
Department of Psychology. I’ve been enjoying it so far and I’m looking
forward to ramping up my research in the next few years. Aside from that
I’m also an intern/research analyst at UCSF School Health and Evaluation
Research. I feel incredibly lucky to apply some of the knowledge from my
graduate training to work on projects that directly make an impact on
youth mental health in California!
On this blog you’ll find some writing about my research. Writing
definitely helps me parse through challenging ideas (and my notes app on
my computer is already at 10GB LOL). I’m interested in comparing how
estimation algorithms produce different parameter estimates in hard to
estimate latent class models. Also, I’m currently exploring how
different types of parameter restrictions in latent class models impacts
estimation. If you read anything interesting and you’d like to chat,
please DM me on Twitter @croutontheory. I
don’t want to put my email because I’m afraid of SPAM BOTS.
When I’m not doing research, you can find me at whatever new
restaurant or cafe that legit just opened 30 seconds ago in Seattle. I’m
trying to collate all of my seattle food spots on this page so stay
tuned. I spend so much money eating out I might as well document it.
[Disclaimer! The things I write on this blog do not reflect the
opinions/views of the institutions that I work at, or my advisor! All
thoughts (and mistakes) are my own..]
